==Personal life==
Osbourne and his wife, Lisa Stelly, have a daughter, Pearl Clementine Osbourne, born on 24 April 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/05/07/hello-jack-osbourne-lisa-stelly-pearl-clementine-first-photo/ |title=Jack Osbourne Introduces Pearl Clementine |accessdate=2012-05-07 |date=2012-05-07 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> Osbourne and Stelly were married in Hawaii on 7 October 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Garcia|first=Jennifer|title=Jack Osbourne Marries Lisa Stelly|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20636929,00.html|accessdate=8 October 2012|newspaper=People|date=2012-10-08}}</ref> In August 2013, Osbourne and his wife announced they were expecting their second child,{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} but on 6 September 2013, Osbourne's wife Lisa revealed she suffered a miscarriage in her second trimester; they had been expecting a son. He would have been named Theo.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://celebritybabies.people.com/2013/09/06/jack-osbourne-lisa-osbourne-miscarriage/|title = Jack and Lisa Osbourne Lose Their Baby Boy|date = 6 September 2013|last = Rouse|first = Wade|publisher = People}}</ref> Their second child, daughter Andy Rose Osbourne, was born on 13 June 2015.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://us.hellomagazine.com/healthandbeauty/mother-and-baby/2015061725842/exclusive-jack-osbourne-welcomes-baby-girl-/ | title=Exclusive: Jack Osbourne and wife Lisa welcome baby girl| work = [[Hello!]] | date= 17 June 2015| accessdate=19 June 2015 | archivedate=19 June 2015| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20150619024132/http://us.hellomagazine.com/healthandbeauty/mother-and-baby/2015061725842/exclusive-jack-osbourne-welcomes-baby-girl-/ | deadurl=no}}</ref> They welcomed their third child, daughter Minnie Theodora Osbourne, on 3 February 2018.<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/Be04-csD7p_/?hl=en&taken-by=jackosbourne</ref> The couple announced their separation on 18 May 2018.<ref>http://people.com/tv/jack-osbourne-wife-lisa-files-for-divorce/</ref>

In June 2012, Osbourne announced that he had been diagnosed with [[Multiple sclerosis#Clinical courses|relapsing-remitting]] [[multiple sclerosis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-18478530|title=Jack Osbourne diagnosed with MS, Ozzy and Sharon reveal|accessdate=2012-06-18}}</ref> He had experienced symptoms for a number of years including blindness in one eye; numbness in both legs; and problems with his bladder, bowel, and stomach.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2162345/Jack-Osbourne-Multiple-Sclerosis-diagnosis-Star-says-hes-fine-appears-The-Talk-mother-Sharon.html|title = 'I AM NOT DYING!' Jack Osbourne takes MS diagnosis in his stride as he urges people to 'stop sensationalising' his illness|publisher = Mail Online|last = Daily Mail Reporter|date = 21 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jack Osbourne has had symptoms of multiple sclerosis for "three or four years"|url=http://home.nzcity.co.nz/news/article.aspx?id=149344&fm=newsmain,nrhl|accessdate=7 February 2013|newspaper=NZ City|date=23 June 2012}}</ref> Osbourne injects [[Glatiramer acetate|Copaxone]] medication daily, uses vitamin supplements and hormone replacement therapy, and has travelled to Europe for stem cell therapy.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.blisstree.com/2013/05/22/public-health-2/alternative-medicine/jack-osbourne-multiple-sclerosis-paleo/|title = Jack Osbourne Goes Paleo And Does Stem Cell Treatment For MS|publisher = Blisstree|last = Murphy|first = Carrie|date = 22 May 2013}}</ref><ref name="people.com">[http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20615865,00.html Jack Osbourne 'my Life Is Far from Over' : People.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He has also made lifestyle changes such as minimising stress, exercising regularly, and significantly altering his diet.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/115754/Jack-Osbourne-Opens-Up-On-Living-With-MS-I-Dont-How-Long-Things-Will-Be-Good-For|title = Jack Osbourne Opens Up On Living With MS: 'I Don't Know How Long Things Will Be Good For'|publisher = Entertainment Wise|first = Shaun|date = 24 May 2013|last = Kitchener|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130707015820/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/115754/Jack-Osbourne-Opens-Up-On-Living-With-MS-I-Dont-How-Long-Things-Will-Be-Good-For|archivedate = 7 July 2013|df = dmy-all}}</ref> However, he has spoken of his fear of a rapid decline and has admitted that his doctors have urged him to stop participating in highly intensive physical workouts: "Right now am I going to be in a wheelchair? No. But if I don't take care of myself, who knows."<ref name="people.com"/><ref name="entertainmentwise.com">{{Cite web|url = http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/115754/Jack-Osbourne-Opens-Up-On-Living-With-MS-I-Dont-How-Long-Things-Will-Be-Good-For|title = Jack Osbourne Opens Up On Living With MS: 'I Don't Know How Long Things Will Be Good For'|publisher = Entertainment Wise|date = 24 May 2013|last = Kitchener|first = Shaun|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130707015820/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/115754/Jack-Osbourne-Opens-Up-On-Living-With-MS-I-Dont-How-Long-Things-Will-Be-Good-For|archivedate = 7 July 2013|df = dmy-all}}
</ref> While appearing on ''Dancing with the Stars'' in October 2013, Osbourne said that he did not suffer from "any severe symptoms other than the odd bit of tingling down my leg and the occasional bout of fatigue."<ref>https://www.facebook.com/JackOsbourneOfficial/posts/688787791140157</ref>

